description.narrative: (Georgia): .With FY 2018 funds, G4G will provide technical assistance and training to the Georgian government, private sector, business associations, academic institutions, and think tanks to support Georgia's efforts to develop a predictable business environment in which legal and regulatory frameworks are fairly and transparently applied. To promote transparency and accountability in the reform-making process, G4G will facilitate public-private dialogues on topics such as EU integration, energy market trading, water resource allocation, insolvency, and capital market reform... ..With G4G support, Georgia passed legislation that mandates the Georgian government to undertake Regulatory Impact Assessments (RIA) for all major policy changes or laws starting January 1, 2019. While the RIA process is now institutionalized on paper, the full economy- and government-wide adoption of RIAs may take some time. G4G will ensure effectiveness and accountability to the American taxpayer (JSP 4.1) by undertaking RIAs of priority reforms while providing coaching and peer review assistance to build the culture for evidence-based analysis that will last beyond the life of the project... ..G4G will also support the Georgian government to analyze transaction settlement options for the newly-liberalized energy market, develop a training course on taxation for vocational students, provide training and technical assistance to the Revenue Service on post clearance audits for authorized economic operators, support the Georgian government in the implementation of the pension law communication strategy, and assess opportunities for adopting innovative digital tools, such as blockchain, in line with Georgian government's digital government initiatives. These market-oriented reforms will create a predictable business environment, expand business opportunities for Georgia's citizens (ICS MO 2.1 and JRS 2.2), and create a better market for U.S. exports and investment (JSP 2.3 and JRS 2.1)..
